    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That analogy is helpful. I'm just worried about some students who might bring up the idea that substantive due process is too subjective or that it lets judges basically make up laws based on their own views. How should I handle that critique? Should I tell them that those arguments are just trying to undermine fundamental rights?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
